courseWork.title: Grading Sheet for Calpurnia Tate Final Project
Calpurnia Tate Final Project
courseWork.description:
Recognizing Authorâs Purpose 				 Name_______________________
The Evolution of Calpurnia Tate     

Authors write books for a variety of reasons. Sometimes an author is trying to teach (or inform) the reader, sometimes the purpose is to entertain the reader, and sometimes it is to persuade (or convince) the reader. 

Jacqueline Kelly manages to do all three in The Evolution of Calpurnia Tate. 

Write a letter to a friend recommending this book to them. You will explain that it informs, entertains and persuades the reader. Give examples from the text to support your thinking. You will also need to include one quote for each body paragraph. 

Start with an introduction paragraph. Briefly tell what the book is about.
Paragraph two will explain how the author informs the reader. 
Paragraph three will explain how the author entertains the reader.
Paragraph four will explain how the author persuades the reader. 
End with a concluding paragraph. 

Each body paragraph will need a transition sentence that explains what the focus of the paragraph will be. 

For each body paragraph give at least 3 examples that explain the topic of that paragraph.
courseWork.descriptionHtml:
Recognizing Authorâs Purpose Name_______________________
The Evolution of Calpurnia Tate

Authors write books for a variety of reasons. Sometimes an author is trying to teach (or inform) the reader, sometimes the purpose is to entertain the reader, and sometimes it is to persuade (or convince) the reader.

Jacqueline Kelly manages to do all three in The Evolution of Calpurnia Tate.

Write a letter to a friend recommending this book to them. You will explain that it informs, entertains and persuades the reader. Give examples from the text to support your thinking. You will also need to include one quote for each body paragraph.

Start with an introduction paragraph. Briefly tell what the book is about.
Paragraph two will explain how the author informs the reader.
Paragraph three will explain how the author entertains the reader.
Paragraph four will explain how the author persuades the reader.
End with a concluding paragraph.

Each body paragraph will need a transition sentence that explains what the focus of the paragraph will be.

For each body paragraph give at least 3 examples that explain the topic of that paragraph.
